name: CAP_PAY_EL_WITHHELD_CAP
description: This table indicates whether each rate element in a formula caused the capitation payment to be withheld.

columns.name: TX_ID
columns.description: The unique identifier (.1 item) for the transaction record.

columns.name: GROUP_LINE
columns.description: The line number for the information associated with this record.

columns.name: VALUE_LINE
columns.description: The line number of one of the multiple values associated with a specific group of data within this record.

columns.name: WITHHELD_YN
columns.description: If this rate element is configured to withhold capitation payments when a default value is used, this item will indicate whether this rate element caused a payment to be withheld.
